---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import TimeLineElement from "../components/cv/TimeLine.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Resume" sideBarActiveItemID="cv">
  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Profile</div>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-6 text-justify">
    <p class="max-w-3xl">
      Abhishek Singh — Backend Engineer focused on Java and Spring Boot. I build secure, scalable microservices and APIs
      with JWT authentication, JPA/Hibernate, and well‑designed data models on PostgreSQL/MySQL. Comfortable with
      in‑memory caching, structured logging (Kafka), timezone‑safe utilities, Docker‑based deployments and AWS.
      Recently, as a Java Backend Intern at PolicyBazaar (Aug–Nov 2025, Gurugram), I delivered a production healthcare
      consultation microservice enabling online/offline doctor bookings, patient profiling and payment tracking; integrated
      partner REST APIs; added robust validation, caching and observability; and implemented AiSHA health‑data endpoints
      (metrics/graphs and authenticated POST writes).
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Education</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container grid gap-4 mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Bachelor of Technology — Information Technology"
      subtitle="2021 – 2025 · Dr APJ Abdul Kalam Technical University, Lucknow"
    />
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Experience</div>
  </div>

  <div class="time-line-container mb-10">
    <TimeLineElement
      title="Java Backend Intern — PolicyBazaar.com"
      subtitle="Aug 2025 – Nov 2025 · On-site Gurugram"
    >
      Built a Spring Boot microservice for healthcare consultations (doctor bookings, patient profiling, payment status).
      Integrated JWT-secured partner REST APIs with JPA persistence and Kafka-based structured logging.
      Added robust validation, in-memory caching and date/time utilities for reliable, timezone-aware processing.
      Implemented AiSHA health-data APIs (graphs and POST endpoints) with proper JWT authentication and DB writes.
    </TimeLineElement>
    <TimeLineElement
      title="AI Researcher — Coding Jr"
      subtitle="Jan 2025 – Feb 2025 · Remote"
    >
      Built a custom Copilot using open Large Language Models and fine-tuned it for a specific use case.
    </TimeLineElement>
  </div>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Certifications</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc mx-6 mb-10 grid gap-2">
    <li>
      Machine Learning Data Science Program — Greeks for Greeks (Apr 2024 – Sep 2024)
    </li>
  </ul>

  <div class="mb-5">
    <div class="text-3xl w-full font-bold">Skills</div>
  </div>

  <ul class="list-disc md:columns-3 columns-2 mx-6">
    <li>Java</li>
    <li>Spring Boot</li>
    <li>Git</li>
    <li>Docker</li>
    <li>SQL (PostgreSQL, MySQL)</li>
    <li>AWS</li>
    <li>Linux</li>
    <li>Scikit-learn</li>
    <li>Python</li>
    <li>C++</li>
    <li>Machine Learning</li>
    <li>Flutter</li>
    <li>Data Structures & Algorithms</li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
